Question: What is the precondition for the ECB to invite a non-EU country
  authority to a college of supervisors or enter into an MoU with it?
Example answer: A positive equivalence assessment of the confidentiality regime is a
  pre-condition for the ECB to invite a non-EU country authority to a
  college or enter into an MoU with it, and confidential supervisory
  information is shared on a need-to-know basis. (ECB Supervisory
  Manual, page 30)
