  covered by SSM thematic reviews of significant institutions. -
  D/SSR’s involvement:   - In setting topics: D/SSR coordinates the
  identification of potential thematic review topics in liaison with
  JSTs, directorates‑general, national competent authorities and other
  stakeholders, and ensures those topics align with the Supervisory
  Board’s priorities.   - In conducting thematic work (second line of
  defence): D/SSR performs horizontal analyses and SREP benchmarking,
  coordinates thematic work, monitors follow‑up on supervisory
  findings and measures, and proposes improvements to supervisory
  policies and methodologies.
